work of a skilled craftsman into that of a consummate artist. Demonstrating an impressive command of the vast scholarship on this iconic composer, Caeyers brings Beethoven's world alive with elegant prose, memorable musical descriptions, and vivid depictions of Bonn and Vienna-the cities where Beethoven produced and performed his works. Caeyers explores how Beethoven's career was impacted by the historical and philosophical shifts taking place in the music world, and conversely, how his own trajectory changed the course of the music industry. Equal parts absorbing cultural history and lively biography, Beethoven, A Life paints a complex portrait of the musical genius who redefined the musical style of his day and went on to become one of the great pillars of Western art music.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aComposerszAustriavBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Entertainment & Performing Arts.2bisacsh  aBeethoven's career.  aBonn.  aVienna.  aartistic direction.  abeethoven biography.  acomposer.  acomposition.  acontext.  adeafness.  adisability.  adisabled artists.  agenius.  ahistory.  ainnovation.  alate 18th century.  amusic biographies.  amusic scholars.  amusical impact.  apiano music.  astory.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2021z9783110753783oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2021 Englishz978311075403208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520975026zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/978052097502642